	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002091_0001"/><!--pb/@n='109-1'-->
<lb/><p rend="right">19<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> Oct<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> 1864 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Hooker</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I wrote to <persName>D<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Kirk</persName>
<lb/>requesting him to say 
<lb/>if the proposition 
<lb/>made were agreeable 
<lb/>and that I had <del type="strikethrough">a 
<lb/>form of</del><add place="above">an</add> application 
<lb/>to <persName>Earl Russell</persName>
<lb/>all ready to send 
<lb/>off as soon as I 
<lb/>knew that he 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002091_0002"/><!--pb/@n='109-2'-->
<lb/>was satisfied with 
<lb/>the salary proposed<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>But I sent it to 
<lb/><placeName>Edinburgh</placeName> and 
<lb/>today hearing that 
<lb/>he is gone to <placeName>Kew</placeName>
<lb/>I write to ask 
<lb/>you to ascertain 
<lb/>his mind and 
<lb/>oblige<reg>.</reg> Yours ever </p>
<lb/><p><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
